<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 24 at 3:36PM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...DETERIORATING ROAD CONDITIONS EXPECTED FOR WESTERN NEW YORK...
Light snow across western New York will increase in intensity for
a few hours into the early evening. Snow will accumulate quicker
on area roadways. With the sun setting and temperatures dropping,
earlier wet roads will re-freeze if not well treated. The
combination of accumulating snow and re- freezing roads, will
cause driving conditions to deteriorate through the evening
commute.
The increased snowfall rate will also cause reduced visibilities
to a quarter mile at times. If traveling, allow extra time to
reach your destination and allow extra space between you and the
vehicle in front of you.</description>
